455", "ce:indexed-name": "Manotum R."}, {"preferred-name": {"ce:given-name": "R.", "ce:initials": "R.", "ce:surname": "Klinkla", "ce:indexed-name": "Klinkla R."}, "@seq": "2", "ce:initials": "R.", "@_fa": "true", "@type": "auth", "ce:surname": "Klinkla", "@auid": "56449212000", "ce:indexed-name": "Klinkla R."}, {"preferred-name": {"ce:given-name": "N.", "ce:initials": "N.", "ce:surname": "Phaisangittisakul", "ce:indexed-name": "Phaisangittisakul N."}, "@seq": "3", "ce:initials": "N.", "@_fa": "true", "@type": "auth", "ce:surname": "Phaisangittisakul", "@auid": "6603363146", "ce:indexed-name": "Phaisangittisakul N."}, {"preferred-name": {"ce:given-name": "U.", "ce:initials": "U.", "ce:surname": "Pinsook", "ce:indexed-name": "Pinsook U."}, "@seq": "4", "ce:initials": "U.", "@date-locked": "2017-11-30T18:27:09.026", "@_fa": "true", "@type": "auth", "ce:surname": "Pinsook", "@auid": "6603473659", "ce:indexed-name": "Pinsook U."}, {"preferred-name": {"ce:given-name": "T.", "ce:initials": "T.", "ce:surname": "Bovornratanaraks", "ce:indexed-name": "Bovornratanaraks T."}, "@seq": "5", "ce:initials": "T.", "@_fa": "true", "@type": "auth", "ce:surname": "Bovornratanaraks", "@auid": "24334134600", "ce:indexed-name": "Bovornratanaraks T."}]}], "citation-title": "Effect of Pressure on the Stability and Electronic Structure of ZnO0.5S0.5 and ZnO0.5Se0.5", "abstracts": "\u00a9 2017, The Minerals, Metals & Materials Society.Structures and high-pressure phase transitions in ZnO0.5S0.5 and ZnO0.5Se0.5 have been investigated using density functional theory calculations. The previously proposed structures of ZnO0.5S0.5 and ZnO0.5Se0.5 which are chalcopyrite (I4 \u00af 2 d), rocksalt (Fm3 m), wurtzite (P6 3mc) and CuAu-I (P4 \u00af m2) have been fully investigated. Stabilities of these materials have been systematically studied up to 40 GPa using various approaches. We have confirmed the stability of the chalcopyrite structure up to 30 GPa for which the CuAu-I structure has been previously proposed. However, our calculation revealed that CuAu-I is not a stable structure under 32 GPa and 33 GPa for both ZnO0.5S0.5 and ZnO0.5Se0.5, respectively, which could explain the failure in several attempts to fabricate these materials under such conditions. We have also examined the pressure-dependence of the bandgap and electronic structure up to 30 GPa. We can conclude from our PDOS analysis that the applied pressure does not change the atomic state characters of electronic states near the top of valence and the bottom of conduction bands, but mainly modifies the dominant Zn-3d atomic state of the deep Bloch state at \u22121 eV below Fermi level.", "correspondence": {"affiliation": {"country": "Thailand", "postal-code": "10330", "@country": "tha", "city": "Bangkok", "organization": [{"$": "Extreme Conditions Physics Research Laboratory"}, {"$": "Physics of Energy Materials Research Unit"}, {"$": "Department of Physics"}, {"$": "Faculty of Science"}, {"$": "Chulalongkorn University"}]}, "person": {"ce:initials": "T.", "ce:surname": "Bovornratanaraks", "ce:indexed-name": "Bovornratanaraks T."}}, "citation-info": {"author-keywords": {"author-keyword": [{"$": "elastic properties", "@xml:lang": "eng"}, {"$": "high pressure", "@xml:lang": "eng"}, {"$": "II\u2013VI ternary alloys", "@xml:lang": "eng"}, {"$": "Phase stability", "@xml:lang": "eng"}]}, "citation-type": {"@code": "ar"}, "citation-language": {"@language": "English", "@xml:lang": "eng"}, "abstract-language": {"@language": "English", "@xml:lang": "eng"}}, "source": {"codencode": "JECMA", "sourcetitle-abbrev": "J Electron Mater", "@country": "usa", "translated-sourcetitle": {"$": "Journal of Electronic Materials", "@xml:lang": "eng"}, "issn": {"$": "03615235", "@type": "print"}, "volisspag": {"voliss": {"@volume": "46", "@issue": "12"}, "pagerange": {"@first": "6856", "@last": "6863"}}, "@type": "j", "publicationyear": {"@first": "2017"}, "publisher": {"publishername": "Springer New York LLC", "ce:e-addre